    "body": "Well I don't know the internals, but whatever updates the `div` containing the output, could just call javascript:\n\n```\nmydiv.scrollTop=mydiv.scrollHeight\n```\n\n[Here](https://jsfiddle.net/birnstiel/7mvh2tuc/3/embedded/result/) is an example: the button changes the content of the scrollable div, and then scrolls to the bottom of it.\n\nAgain: I don't know if this is feasible to include, but if above code could be implemented, it should be browser independent (just needs javascript).\n"
